featured_reviews.review_id:
Triplicane Big Mosque (also called Wallajah Mosque) is a mosque located in Triplicane High Road, Triplicane in Chennai. Constructed in the Mughal architectural style, the mosque was built in 1795 by the family of Muhammad Ali Khan Wallajah, the Nawab of Arcot during 1765. It has a large prayer hall, a tank and a large ground in front. The entire structure is constructed with granite without the use of iron or wood.

The Nawab of Arcot was a loyal ally of the British who offered him Chepauk Palace where he could house his military and administrative buildings. It is believed that Nawab Muhammad Ali moved to Chepauk, located in Triplicane in 1768. There were around 20,000 Marakayar Muslims who moved with him to the city. It was then the largest community of Muslims in South India after Hyderabad. The Nawab had full control of the region and all the cases were resolved under Muslim Law irrespective of the religion of the accused. Historians believe that after the mosque was built, it added to the cultural mix in Triplicane, which had a famous Hindu temple in Parthasarathy Temple and the Portuguese Christian stronghold of San Thome.

The Nawab of Arcot was friendly towards fellow Hindus, appointing a Hindu as his chief personal secretary. A chronogram written in Persian by Raja Makhhan Lal Bahdur Khirat, the Hindu Munshi of the Nawab, is found on the entrance to the prayer hall. The mosque is the largest and one of the oldest in Chennai and is active as a place of worship. It is administered by Prince of Arcot Endowments Trust. Most of the administrative staff of the mosque are Hindus, symbolizing peaceful coexistence between the two religions.

pllllivaacl | Pallivasal Masjid holds a special place in my heart. This mosque is more than just a place of worship--it's a haven of spirituality and community.

As I step into pllllivaacl | Pallivasal Masjid, I'm enveloped in a sense of peace that's truly unique. The architecture and ambiance create an environment of serenity, where I can connect with my faith and find solace.

What truly sets pllllivaacl | Pallivasal Masjid apart is its role as a center of unity and togetherness. It's not just a mosque; it's a gathering place for people to connect, share their faith, and build meaningful relationships.

The mosque's leaders and community members make it feel like a welcoming and inclusive home. Their hospitality and willingness to share the teachings of Islam create an atmosphere of learning and growth.

Whether I'm seeking a quiet moment of reflection or a chance to connect with fellow believers, pllllivaacl | Pallivasal Masjid is my sanctuary. It's a reminder that faith is a personal journey that becomes even more enriching when shared with a supportive and caring community.

featured_reviews.review_id:
ADDRESS : Triplicane High Road, near Star theater.
BEST THING: One of the oldest Masjid in Tamil Nadu. If you ever want to witness the oldest architecture then here it is standing tall with soo much legacy to speak about. Constructed on a very big space both in and around. More than 800 people can pray at a time.
Parking space is available for both 2 and 4 wheeler.
Also you have lot of Islamic shops around to buy Quran, Hadis, Thasbi, Skull cabs, etc.
There is one Dharga near by the Masjid as well.
If you ever feel so depressed or sad just visit the place and am sure you will feel lighter than ever before.
OVERALL: No words to explain the beauty of this monumental historic Masjid that stands tall till date.
